properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 29 at 9:18AM PST until March 1 at 9:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds increasing to 20 to 30 mph with gusts up
to 50 mph expected.

* WHERE...Antelope Valley. Strongest in the foothills and western
valley.

* WHEN...Until 9 PM PST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds and reduced visibility from blowing dust
will make driving difficult. Gusty winds could blow around
unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few
power outages may result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Highway 14, especially between Acton and
Palmdale, and Highway 138 will be most impacted by the gusty
winds.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM PST SUNDAY
